<!-- ═══════════════ ABOUT ═══════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="overline">The Destination</p>
    <div class="about-layout">
      <div class="about-left">
        <h2>What is Little Boracay?</h2>
        <p class="body-lg speakable">
          <strong>Little Boracay</strong> is a natural tidal sandbar off the western coastline of <strong>Calatagan, Batangas</strong>, facing the South China Sea. It earned its name from a striking resemblance to the famous Boracay Island — white sand, turquoise-clear shallow water — but reachable from Metro Manila without a flight.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike a beach resort, Little Boracay is entirely natural — a shifting sandbar that changes with the tides. Visitors arrive by short boat transfer from Calatagan's coast, where iconic <strong>floating bamboo cottages</strong> are anchored over the shallow water.
        </p>
        <div class="feat-row">
          <div class="feat-item">
            <div class="feat-icon">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Natural sandbar</strong>
              <span>Not a resort — pure nature</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feat-item">
            <div class="feat-icon">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 16.5a6 6 0 0 1-6 6H4a4 4 0 0 1-4-4 4 4 0 0 1 4-4h1a6 6 0 0 1 6-6 6 6 0 0 1 6 6h1a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Boat access only</strong>
              <span>Short transfer from Calatagan</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feat-item">
            <div class="feat-icon">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"/><polyline points="9 22 9 12 15 12 15 22"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Floating cottages</strong>
              <span>Bamboo over shallow water</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="feat-item">
            <div class="feat-icon">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>3–4 hours from Manila</strong>
              <span>No flight required</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-facts">
        <div class="facts-header">Quick Facts</div>
        <div class="facts-list">
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Type</span><strong>Natural tidal sandbar</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Location</span><strong>Calatagan, Batangas, PH</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Coordinates</span><strong>13.8198°N · 120.6158°E</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Body of water</span><strong>South China Sea</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Access</span><strong>Boat only from coast</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>From Manila</span><strong>3–4 hour drive</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Best time</span><strong>Morning low tide</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Peak season</span><strong>November – May</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Hours</span><strong>8:00 AM – 5:00 PM</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>TripAdvisor</span><strong>★ 4.3 · Travelers' Choice</strong></div>
        </div>
        <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/dDyEJhYkpxW2gxCt8" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="facts-map-btn">
          <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2C8.13 2 5 5.13 5 9c0 5.25 7 13 7 13s7-7.75 7-13c0-3.87-3.13-7-7-7zm0 9.5c-1.38 0-2.5-1.12-2.5-2.5s1.12-2.5 2.5-2.5 2.5 1.12 2.5 2.5-1.12 2.5-2.5 2.5z"/></svg>
          View on Google Maps
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ ACTIVITIES ═══════════════ -->
<section class="section section-alt" id="activities">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="overline">Things To Do</p>
    <h2>Activities at Little Boracay</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Whether it's your first visit or your tenth, the sandbar always delivers.</p>

    <div class="act-grid">
      <div class="act-card">
        <div class="act-num">01</div>
        <h3>Boat Tours to the Sandbar</h3>
        <p>Local operators run short transfers from Calatagan's coastal barangays to the sandbar. Book in advance on weekends and holidays.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="act-card act-featured">
        <div class="act-num">02</div>
        <div class="act-badge">Most Popular</div>
        <h3>Floating Cottage Experience</h3>
        <p>The signature activity. Bamboo cottages anchored over crystal-clear shallow water — relax, eat, swim, and take in open sea views on all sides.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="act-card">
        <div class="act-num">03</div>
        <h3>Swimming</h3>
        <p>Calm, warm, shallow waters with clear visibility to the sandy bottom. Suitable for all ages including families with young children.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="act-card">
        <div class="act-num">04</div>
        <h3>Snorkeling</h3>
        <p>Clear coastal waters reveal marine life around the sandbar. Bring your own gear for the best experience exploring the underwater environment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="act-card">
        <div class="act-num">05</div>
        <h3>Photography &amp; Drone</h3>
        <p>One of Batangas' most photogenic destinations. Aerial drone photography over the tidal sandbar at low tide is spectacular.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="act-card">
        <div class="act-num">06</div>
        <h3>Day Trips from Manila</h3>
        <p>Leave Manila early, arrive at the sandbar by 9AM, spend the day, and be back in Manila by evening. The perfect quick coastal escape.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ PLAN A VISIT ═══════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="visit">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="overline">How to Get There</p>
    <h2>Plan Your Visit</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Everything you need for the perfect Calatagan sandbar day trip from Manila.</p>

    <div class="visit-layout">
      <div class="visit-steps-col">
        <div class="v-step">
          <div class="vstep-n">01</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Drive from Metro Manila</h3>
            <p>Take the <strong>South Luzon Expressway (SLEX)</strong> south, then merge onto the <strong>STAR Tollway</strong> toward Batangas. The drive is <strong>3–4 hours</strong> under normal traffic. Leave by 5–6 AM on weekends.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="v-step">
          <div class="vstep-n">02</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Navigate to Calatagan</h3>
            <p>Exit toward <strong>Lian, Batangas</strong> then follow roads to Calatagan town. Use Google Maps or Waze. Nearby landmarks: <em>CaSoBe, Stilts Beach Resort</em>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="v-step">
          <div class="vstep-n">03</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Reach the Jump-Off Point</h3>
            <p>Head to the coastal barangays of Calatagan where local boat operators run transfers. Contact operators in advance on weekends — floating cottages fill up fast.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="v-step">
          <div class="vstep-n">04</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Boat to the Sandbar</h3>
            <p>The boat ride takes <strong>10–20 minutes</strong> depending on conditions. Always confirm with operators the day before — boats may not run in rough weather.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-title">Essential Tips</div>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>Bring cash (PHP)</strong> — most operators don't accept cards</li>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>Leave by 5–6 AM</strong> on weekends to beat SLEX traffic</li>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>Book cottages ahead</strong> — fills up on peak weekends</li>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>High SPF sunscreen</strong> — reflected water sun is intense</li>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>Dry bag</strong> for phone, wallet, and electronics</li>
            <li><span class="tip-check">✓</span><strong>Check PAGASA</strong> — rough weather cancels boats</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="seasons-row">
          <div class="season-pill season-good">
            <strong>Nov – May</strong>
            <span>Dry season — best conditions</span>
          </div>
          <div class="season-pill season-warn">
            <strong>Jun – Oct</strong>
            <span>Typhoon season — check first</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- PLAN A VISIT FORM -->
      <div class="form-panel" id="plan-form">
        <div class="form-panel-header">
          <h3>Send Me a Visitor Guide</h3>
          <p>Tell us when you're coming and we'll send you everything you need to know.</p>
        </div>
        <form id="planForm" novalidate>
          <div class="field-row">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="p-name">Full Name *</label>
              <input type="text" id="p-name" placeholder="Juan dela Cruz" required />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="p-email">Email Address *</label>
              <input type="email" id="p-email" placeholder="juan@email.com" required />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-row">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="p-date">Planned Visit Date</label>
              <input type="date" id="p-date" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="p-guests">Group Size</label>
              <select id="p-guests">
                <option value="">Select...</option>
                <option>Solo / couple (1–2)</option>
                <option>Small group (3–5)</option>
                <option>Medium group (6–10)</option>
                <option>Large group (11–20)</option>
                <option>Event / 20+</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="p-type">Type of Visit</label>
            <select id="p-type">
              <option value="">Select...</option>
              <option>Day trip with floating cottage</option>
              <option>Family outing</option>
              <option>Barkada / friend group</option>
              <option>Corporate / team building</option>
              <option>Photography / drone shoot</option>
              <option>Special occasion</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="p-from">Travelling from</label>
            <input type="text" id="p-from" placeholder="e.g. Makati, BGC, Quezon City..." />
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="p-notes">Questions or special requests</label>
            <textarea id="p-notes" rows="3" placeholder="Dietary needs, accessibility, large group logistics..."></textarea>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="form-submit" id="planBtn">
            Send My Visit Plan
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="form-success" id="planOk">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#166534" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg>
            <div>
              <strong>You're all set!</strong>
              <p>We'll send your full Little Boracay visitor guide. See you at the sandbar!</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ REVIEWS ═══════════════ -->
<section class="section section-alt" id="reviews">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="overline">What Visitors Say</p>
    <h2 style="text-align:center;">Trusted by Travelers</h2>
    <p class="section-intro" style="text-align:center;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">Real experiences from visitors to Little Boracay sandbar in Calatagan, Batangas.</p>

